1
00:00:00,460 --> 00:00:03,330
Chiaki, you like that girl, don't you?

2
00:00:03,330 --> 00:00:06,030
- Like?
- I heard Anna is leaving the group,

3
00:00:06,030 --> 00:00:08,440
so let's do our best, three of us!

4
00:00:08,440 --> 00:00:10,790
I really want to join you, Director.

5
00:00:10,790 --> 00:00:11,950
Ama.

6
00:00:11,950 --> 00:00:14,320
I've always wanted to apologize to you.

7
00:00:14,320 --> 00:00:16,390
Just once, let me talk to you.

8
00:00:16,390 --> 00:00:18,220
Please contact me.

9
00:00:18,220 --> 00:00:19,950
That movie audition was today, right?

10
00:00:19,950 --> 00:00:23,080
I can only really become a character

11
00:00:23,080 --> 00:00:26,480
if I've experienced something similar myself.

12
00:00:26,480 --> 00:00:29,740
Experience it all with me.

13
00:00:29,740 --> 00:00:31,340
Ama.

14
00:00:31,340 --> 00:00:33,450
Go out with me.

15
00:00:35,710 --> 00:00:39,660
But I can't ask that of you,
just so I can act.

16
00:00:39,660 --> 00:00:41,710
It's not about acting.

17
00:00:42,480 --> 00:00:43,470
Huh?

18
00:00:43,470 --> 00:00:46,860
I don't want anyone else to have you.

19
00:00:46,860 --> 00:00:49,220
I want you to be mine.

20
00:00:51,540 --> 00:00:53,070
What?

21
00:00:53,070 --> 00:00:55,320
Is it that surprising?

22
00:00:55,320 --> 00:00:58,790
I mean, we're talking about you and me.

23
00:00:58,790 --> 00:01:02,470
We live in two different worlds.

24
00:01:02,470 --> 00:01:04,160
I like you.

25
00:01:05,210 --> 00:01:10,290
You're kind, straightforward,
and you give it your all.

26
00:01:15,090 --> 00:01:17,710
What do you think of me, Ama?

27
00:01:20,640 --> 00:01:22,650
You're...

28
00:01:23,700 --> 00:01:28,050
You're... a very important mentor to me.

29
00:01:29,190 --> 00:01:30,940
That's it?

30
00:01:32,890 --> 00:01:34,320
Don't hide.

31
00:01:34,320 --> 00:01:36,440
Look at me.

32
00:01:43,540 --> 00:01:44,940
Do you hate me?

33
00:01:50,270 --> 00:01:52,540
So, do you like me?

34
00:02:01,940 --> 00:02:04,060
If that's the case,

35
00:02:05,030 --> 00:02:07,340
how about a trial run?

36
00:02:09,160 --> 00:02:14,270
Until the audition,
just think of it as using me.

37
00:02:15,510 --> 00:02:17,670
Using you?

38
00:02:19,340 --> 00:02:21,190
I'd feel bad.

39
00:02:21,190 --> 00:02:23,220
Don't.

40
00:02:27,480 --> 00:02:29,340
I want to try...

41
00:02:30,830 --> 00:02:33,330
to make you like me.

42
00:02:38,970 --> 00:02:40,530
So...

43
00:02:41,950 --> 00:02:43,600
please.

44
00:02:50,250 --> 00:02:55,060
If you're really okay
with someone like me.

45
00:02:59,720 --> 00:03:01,450
I'm so happy.

46
00:03:55,986 --> 00:03:58,238
Excuse me, Mr. Chiaki?

47
00:03:58,930 --> 00:04:00,690
What?

48
00:04:00,690 --> 00:04:04,860
To be honest, this is my first time
going out with someone.

49
00:04:04,860 --> 00:04:07,130
So, well...

50
00:04:12,680 --> 00:04:14,310
Good.

51
00:04:15,650 --> 00:04:17,430
I'm glad.

52
00:04:19,220 --> 00:04:20,820
<i>Wait.</i>

53
00:04:20,820 --> 00:04:25,740
<i>This is what I think it is, right?</i>

54
00:04:25,740 --> 00:04:28,400
<i>I have to close my eyes.</i>

55
00:04:40,800 --> 00:04:45,360
I'll call you "Ama" from now on.

56
00:04:48,910 --> 00:04:54,080
You call me "Chiaki" too.

57
00:04:55,770 --> 00:04:57,630
Chiaki.

58
00:04:59,060 --> 00:05:02,950
Sorry, on second thoughts, I can't do this!

59
00:05:02,950 --> 00:05:07,310
It's okay. I'll wait until you're ready.

60
00:05:24,620 --> 00:05:26,110
Ama.

61
00:05:26,910 --> 00:05:29,280
Watch your fingers.

62
00:05:29,280 --> 00:05:30,800
Okay.

63
00:05:34,580 --> 00:05:39,490
<i>I've always been scared of falling in love.</i>

64
00:05:42,470 --> 00:05:45,350
Stop!

65
00:05:47,100 --> 00:05:48,490
<i>But...</i>

66
00:05:49,201 --> 00:05:51,541
<i>if it's Mr. Chiaki...</i>

67
00:05:53,580 --> 00:05:55,740
Go out with me.

68
00:06:04,071 --> 00:06:05,160
Here.

69
00:06:05,160 --> 00:06:06,390
Huh?

70
00:06:08,070 --> 00:06:10,170
Don't tell me.

71
00:06:10,170 --> 00:06:12,460
You're serious about her?

72
00:06:14,820 --> 00:06:18,630
You of all people?

73
00:06:27,940 --> 00:06:30,230
I want to cherish her.

74
00:06:37,290 --> 00:06:38,660
Here.

75
00:06:38,660 --> 00:06:40,040
I don't want it.

76
00:06:40,040 --> 00:06:41,340
Huh?

77
00:06:42,360 --> 00:06:44,020
Good for you,

78
00:06:44,720 --> 00:06:46,990
to be able to find someone like that.

79
00:06:52,790 --> 00:06:56,010
I wonder if I'll ever fall in love again.

80
00:06:57,390 --> 00:06:59,220
What happened?

81
00:07:00,270 --> 00:07:02,050
Well...

82
00:07:04,130 --> 00:07:07,430
I ran into a girl I used to like.

83
00:07:08,430 --> 00:07:10,140
Oh.

84
00:07:10,920 --> 00:07:14,120
I forced my number on her, but...

85
00:07:14,960 --> 00:07:17,530
I don't think it's gonna happen.

86
00:07:20,150 --> 00:07:22,490
You're usually more confident.

87
00:07:24,750 --> 00:07:26,470
It's because...

88
00:07:27,980 --> 00:07:30,430
I hurt her.

89
00:07:34,170 --> 00:07:37,050
Senpai, if you're ever struggling,

90
00:07:37,050 --> 00:07:39,810
please don't hesitate to lean on me.

91
00:07:43,090 --> 00:07:44,880
Then...

92
00:07:47,780 --> 00:07:49,770
comfort me.

93
00:07:56,000 --> 00:07:59,530
Stop! Please, stop!

94
00:08:09,000 --> 00:08:10,750
I'm sorry.

95
00:08:17,170 --> 00:08:20,800
That was too much.

96
00:08:27,250 --> 00:08:28,880
<i>Back then,</i>

97
00:08:30,360 --> 00:08:33,210
I was going through a lot.

98
00:08:36,800 --> 00:08:38,860
I wasn't myself.

99
00:08:40,190 --> 00:08:45,100
I mean, that's no excuse, though.

100
00:08:48,190 --> 00:08:50,730
<i>I really regretted it.</i>

101
00:08:52,380 --> 00:08:54,960
<i>What I did was awful.</i>

102
00:09:04,450 --> 00:09:07,260
It's not like you have to give up, right?

103
00:09:09,390 --> 00:09:10,930
Huh?

104
00:09:12,220 --> 00:09:16,330
Just tell her how you feel.

105
00:09:18,770 --> 00:09:22,020
You're better than you were back then, right?

106
00:09:26,260 --> 00:09:28,830
Chiaki!

107
00:09:28,830 --> 00:09:30,630
Stop, you're annoying.

108
00:09:30,630 --> 00:09:33,410
Don't say "annoying". It hurts.

109
00:09:38,820 --> 00:09:41,810
It's an unknown number.

110
00:09:41,810 --> 00:09:43,840
Hurry and answer it.

111
00:09:45,640 --> 00:09:46,920
Yeah.

112
00:09:57,930 --> 00:09:59,070
Hello?

113
00:09:59,070 --> 00:10:02,070
<i>Sorry for calling so late.</i>

114
00:10:02,070 --> 00:10:03,890
<i>It's Minase.</i>

115
00:10:06,800 --> 00:10:08,430
Thank you.

116
00:10:08,430 --> 00:10:12,410
I didn't expect to hear from you.

117
00:10:12,410 --> 00:10:16,790
Kairi-senpai, I'm sorry about the other day.

118
00:10:17,970 --> 00:10:19,970
Don't apologize.

119
00:10:19,970 --> 00:10:23,250
It was all my fault.

120
00:10:24,300 --> 00:10:27,260
<i>Ever since I hurt you,</i>

121
00:10:27,890 --> 00:10:32,050
it's always been weighing on me.

122
00:10:33,690 --> 00:10:35,790
<i>About that,</i>

123
00:10:37,380 --> 00:10:40,120
I'm okay now.

124
00:10:42,180 --> 00:10:46,600
So please, don't worry about it anymore,
Kairi-senpai.

125
00:10:47,900 --> 00:10:50,490
I wanted to tell you that.

126
00:10:55,000 --> 00:10:56,910
Thank you.

127
00:11:00,070 --> 00:11:04,790
<i>But I was so surprised
that you became an actress.</i>

128
00:11:06,180 --> 00:11:09,630
I'm surprised too.

129
00:11:10,320 --> 00:11:12,090
That makes no sense.

130
00:11:16,176 --> 00:11:20,996
I hope we can work on the same set someday.

131
00:11:21,930 --> 00:11:23,650
<i>Me too.</i>

132
00:11:26,210 --> 00:11:29,280
Well, see you.

133
00:11:30,280 --> 00:11:31,880
See you.

134
00:11:44,030 --> 00:11:45,880
Did it go well?

135
00:11:49,780 --> 00:11:51,510
Good for you.

136
00:11:54,520 --> 00:11:56,340
Oh, man.

137
00:11:57,560 --> 00:12:00,240
I really like her.

138
00:12:05,997 --> 00:12:08,470
I really like her!

139
00:12:08,470 --> 00:12:10,488
I told you, you're so annoying.

140
00:12:10,488 --> 00:12:13,730
- I like her!
- You're annoying.

141
00:12:13,730 --> 00:12:16,700
<i>I'm glad we talked things through.</i>

142
00:12:17,670 --> 00:12:21,960
<i>I'll update Mr. Chiaki next time.</i>

143
00:12:25,220 --> 00:12:27,461
[Cast Waiting Room]
I'm scared of the fitness test.

144
00:12:27,461 --> 00:12:28,940
Me too.

145
00:12:28,940 --> 00:12:31,380
A backward jump is crazy.

146
00:12:32,800 --> 00:12:34,586
[Room 205 today]

147
00:12:34,586 --> 00:12:36,860
[Got it! I can't wait!]

148
00:12:36,860 --> 00:12:38,820
Look at this.

149
00:12:38,820 --> 00:12:41,110
- That person is back again.
- Annoying.

150
00:12:41,110 --> 00:12:45,598
I wish Chiaki Hosho would just stop already.

151
00:12:45,598 --> 00:12:47,620
Yeah. He's just a pretty face.

152
00:12:47,620 --> 00:12:49,420
Chiaki Hosho.

153
00:12:49,420 --> 00:12:52,280
How does he get these gigs?

154
00:12:52,280 --> 00:12:54,680
What's this about Chiaki Hosho?

155
00:12:54,680 --> 00:12:56,830
He's so hot!

156
00:12:56,830 --> 00:13:01,030
Nah, you should stay away from him.

157
00:13:01,030 --> 00:13:02,770
Huh?

158
00:13:02,770 --> 00:13:04,580
Why?

159
00:13:04,580 --> 00:13:07,280
He's a scumbag.

160
00:13:07,280 --> 00:13:09,250
Right, Hibiki?

161
00:13:11,230 --> 00:13:12,800
Yeah.

162
00:13:13,490 --> 00:13:18,480
What? Now I'm super curious.

163
00:13:18,480 --> 00:13:21,180
Tell me more.

164
00:13:27,910 --> 00:13:30,221
[Ama Minase]

165
00:13:31,280 --> 00:13:33,810
You've read the script, right?

166
00:13:33,810 --> 00:13:36,530
Yes, of course.

167
00:13:36,530 --> 00:13:41,160
This project has a fairly intense
love scene in the climax.

168
00:13:41,780 --> 00:13:45,430
You're working as an idol too.

169
00:13:45,430 --> 00:13:49,020
Aren't you worried about your public image?

170
00:13:49,020 --> 00:13:51,410
No, I'm fine with it!

171
00:13:51,410 --> 00:13:55,150
I want to work hard as an actress,
so I'll take on any role!

172
00:13:55,150 --> 00:13:57,220
I'll do my best!

173
00:14:00,320 --> 00:14:02,390
I like your enthusiasm.

174
00:14:11,274 --> 00:14:13,992
[Mr. Chiaki]
<i>Wanna come over today?</i>

175
00:14:17,530 --> 00:14:21,530
<i>The audition's over, so I'll head over now.</i>

176
00:14:34,230 --> 00:14:35,920
Welcome.

177
00:14:37,910 --> 00:14:39,380
Ama?

178
00:14:40,060 --> 00:14:44,270
I'm too embarrassed
to invite you to my home now.

179
00:14:45,480 --> 00:14:47,510
Don't say that.

180
00:14:47,510 --> 00:14:49,100
Come in.

181
00:14:50,330 --> 00:14:52,270
Sorry for the intrusion.

182
00:14:55,380 --> 00:14:57,410
Thank you.

183
00:14:57,410 --> 00:14:59,980
It was the final audition, right?

184
00:15:00,770 --> 00:15:02,840
How did it go?

185
00:15:02,840 --> 00:15:07,810
They asked me if I was prepared for it.

186
00:15:07,810 --> 00:15:09,800
Prepared?

187
00:15:09,800 --> 00:15:13,710
The project has a lot of love scenes.

188
00:15:18,710 --> 00:15:20,100
Show me the script.

189
00:15:20,100 --> 00:15:21,570
Sure.

190
00:15:25,050 --> 00:15:28,479
My agency tried to stop me at first.

191
00:15:28,479 --> 00:15:30,110
[A kiss of the nape, overflowing with desire]

192
00:15:30,110 --> 00:15:35,390
But if I get a big role,
it'll open up a lot of opportunities.

193
00:15:35,390 --> 00:15:39,050
I really enjoy acting.

194
00:15:39,050 --> 00:15:41,240
[Kiss her exposed skin]

195
00:15:41,240 --> 00:15:44,300
So I really want to seize this chance.

196
00:15:44,300 --> 00:15:46,780
[Heavy breaths]

197
00:15:46,780 --> 00:15:51,300
I want to give my all
to any role I get from now on.

198
00:15:51,300 --> 00:15:53,690
[Kiss the neckline]

199
00:16:12,820 --> 00:16:14,760
Mr. Chiaki?

200
00:16:16,180 --> 00:16:18,100
I see.

201
00:16:18,860 --> 00:16:20,570
I hope...

202
00:16:21,330 --> 00:16:23,320
that you get the part.

203
00:16:24,924 --> 00:16:26,334
Yeah.

204
00:16:33,200 --> 00:16:35,640
Well, I'll be going.

205
00:16:36,270 --> 00:16:39,090
Okay, good night.

206
00:16:52,140 --> 00:16:56,590
<i>- Hello?</i>
- Director Tanuma, it's been a while.

207
00:16:56,590 --> 00:16:58,390
How have you been?

208
00:16:59,750 --> 00:17:06,110
Actually, there's something
I'd like to discuss with you.

209
00:17:10,270 --> 00:17:13,840
I got the results
for Director Tanuma's audition.

210
00:17:13,840 --> 00:17:15,320
Okay.

211
00:17:17,100 --> 00:17:19,500
Sorry, but you didn't get it.

212
00:17:21,120 --> 00:17:23,620
I see.

213
00:17:23,620 --> 00:17:27,190
But making it to the final round
is a big deal.

214
00:17:27,190 --> 00:17:29,470
Good luck at the next one.

215
00:17:30,410 --> 00:17:32,680
Thank you.

216
00:17:36,040 --> 00:17:41,320
<i>I didn't get the part
in Director Tanuma's movie.</i>

217
00:17:43,920 --> 00:17:45,930
<i>Instead of feeling down,</i>

218
00:17:45,930 --> 00:17:48,820
<i>I have to focus on the work I have now.</i>

219
00:17:51,258 --> 00:17:52,928
Alright!

220
00:17:59,010 --> 00:18:01,800
This is how I feel.

221
00:18:03,580 --> 00:18:04,860
Huh?

222
00:18:05,660 --> 00:18:07,440
You don't get it?

223
00:18:12,850 --> 00:18:14,260
I do.

224
00:18:16,060 --> 00:18:18,350
Your tone says it all.

225
00:18:21,240 --> 00:18:24,650
Let me hear your tone too.

226
00:18:25,810 --> 00:18:28,820
Hey, can I?

227
00:18:31,740 --> 00:18:32,880
- Cut!
- Cut!

228
00:18:32,880 --> 00:18:34,720
- Okay!
- Okay!

229
00:18:34,720 --> 00:18:36,670
That's a wrap! Moving on.

230
00:18:36,670 --> 00:18:38,620
Ms. Minase, your acting was great.

231
00:18:38,620 --> 00:18:40,120
Really?

232
00:18:40,120 --> 00:18:41,770
My heart just skipped a beat.

233
00:18:41,770 --> 00:18:44,140
Oh, I'm glad to hear that.

234
00:18:44,140 --> 00:18:45,800
Thanks for being in this, Hachimura.

235
00:18:45,800 --> 00:18:48,130
Oh, thank you too.

236
00:18:48,130 --> 00:18:49,720
Thank you.

237
00:18:56,990 --> 00:18:59,850
Mr. Chiaki, what's wrong?

238
00:19:01,370 --> 00:19:05,030
I thought you might be feeling down.

239
00:19:06,160 --> 00:19:08,280
That's why you came here?

240
00:19:09,100 --> 00:19:11,000
- Thank...
- Come here.

241
00:19:35,000 --> 00:19:37,970
W-Wait, Mr. Chiaki!

242
00:19:39,860 --> 00:19:42,200
The audition's over.

243
00:19:44,170 --> 00:19:45,560
Huh?

244
00:19:46,390 --> 00:19:48,740
What do you think of me?

245
00:19:52,270 --> 00:19:55,410
You still call me "Mr. Chiaki".

246
00:19:57,240 --> 00:19:59,460
Tell me.

247
00:19:59,460 --> 00:20:02,500
If you don't say it out loud,
I'll get anxious.

248
00:20:04,680 --> 00:20:06,280
I...

249
00:20:16,410 --> 00:20:18,390
That reaction...

250
00:20:20,030 --> 00:20:22,060
Does that mean you like me?

251
00:20:32,071 --> 00:20:33,436
Ama.

252
00:20:34,269 --> 00:20:36,119
Look at me.

253
00:20:49,552 --> 00:20:51,292
I like you,

254
00:20:52,460 --> 00:20:54,630
Chiaki.

255
00:21:02,720 --> 00:21:04,220
Oh, no...

256
00:21:05,560 --> 00:21:08,270
I'm so happy, I might cry.

257
00:21:24,910 --> 00:21:29,840
Promise you'll never stop liking me.

258
00:21:32,130 --> 00:21:33,420
Huh?

259
00:21:37,590 --> 00:21:40,430
I'd never stop liking you.

260
00:21:43,420 --> 00:21:45,050
Never?

261
00:21:45,840 --> 00:21:48,150
You'll always stay by my side?

262
00:21:50,330 --> 00:21:52,820
I'll always be by your side.

263
00:21:54,767 --> 00:21:56,437
Thank you.

264
00:21:58,667 --> 00:22:00,397
It's a promise, okay?

265
00:22:01,511 --> 00:22:03,281
You promised.

266
00:22:24,060 --> 00:22:26,483
<i>Director Tanuma,</i>

267
00:22:26,483 --> 00:22:31,290
<i>there's something
I'd like to discuss with you.</i>

268
00:22:31,290 --> 00:22:33,990
I believe a girl named Ama Minase

269
00:22:33,990 --> 00:22:36,890
<i>is auditioning for your project.</i>

270
00:22:36,890 --> 00:22:41,330
I hear she's actually
not supposed to do love scenes.

271
00:22:41,330 --> 00:22:44,450
Apparently, her agency is forcing her
to do it.

272
00:23:06,470 --> 00:23:07,930
Ama.

273
00:23:09,790 --> 00:23:11,500
I love you.

274
00:23:35,415 --> 00:23:37,480
I love you, I really do.

275
00:23:37,480 --> 00:23:39,160
Don't ever leave me.

276
00:23:39,160 --> 00:23:41,070
Do you have a boyfriend, Ama?

277
00:23:41,070 --> 00:23:42,330
I'm glad to see you.

278
00:23:42,330 --> 00:23:43,520
You look well.

279
00:23:43,520 --> 00:23:45,620
Do you know who her co-star is?

280
